## Tone Adaptation Workflow

- [ ] 1. Identify the source tone — what is the original brand voice and what makes it distinctive?
- [ ] 2. Define the target context — platform, audience, cultural moment, and emotional register
- [ ] 3. Identify the tone delta — what's the same, what's different, what must change
- [ ] 4. Apply the adaptation — rewrite or adapt copy for the new context
- [ ] 5. Preserve brand DNA — ensure the adapted copy still sounds recognizably on-brand
- [ ] 6. Test the adapted copy against the brand voice checklist
- [ ] 7. Document the tone rules for future reference

## Key Inputs
- Original copy: {{original_copy}}
- Source brand/voice: {{source_brand}}
- Target platform/context: {{target_context}}
- Audience: {{audience}}
- Desired tone shift: {{tone_shift}}
